Important update to how Paths execute in your Zaps 

Hi Ai, 

 We're making a system-level improvement to how Paths work in your Zaps. This 
update will make your workflows more reliable and sets the foundation for 
exciting new features we're building. 
What's happening? 
Starting July 22, 2025, we're updating how Paths execute in your Zaps. 
Previously, all branches in a Path ran simultaneously (parallel). Now, they'll 
run in sequence—one after the other. This change will not affect the logic of 
your Zaps, only Path branches where conditions within the branch are met will 
execute, exactly the same as before. 
Will this affect my Zaps? 
In most cases, you'll notice no change. However, Zaps may behave differently 
if: 
 * You have multiple Path branches designed to run at the same time 
 * One Path branch includes steps like Delay, Code, Looping, Digest, or 
Sub-Zaps 
 * You're relying on when a step runs across different branches (not just if 
it runs) Example: If Path A includes a Delay for 1 day, and Path B triggers a 
Slack message immediately—under the new behavior, Path B's steps will be held 
until Path A finishes. This could delay downstream outcomes unless reordered. 
How to mitigate any potential issues: 

 * Check your Path step order: Branches will now run top to bottom and then 
left to right—so the order in which you set them up will matter. 
 * Move time-sensitive steps higher up in the branch list if needed. 
 * Split into multiple Zaps using Sub-Zaps if steps must run in parallel, or 
combine into the same path branch. 
Need more time to adjust? 
If you'd prefer to keep the current parallel execution of Path branches while 
you prepare for this change, we've temporarily added an option in your Zap's 
Advanced Settings. You can toggle "Use parallel Path execution" to maintain the 
parallel behavior. Please note this setting will be available untilSeptember 
30, 2025, after which all Paths will use the new sequential execution. 
Why the change? 
This update is part of our commitment to making Zapier more reliable and 
powerful. The new sequential execution offers: 
 * ✅ More predictable troubleshooting—Paths run in a clear order, making it 
easier to identify and fix issues 
 *  ✅ Fewer rate-limiting errors—Sequential execution reduces the chance of 
hitting rate limits 
 *  ✅ Foundation for future enhancements—This change enables us to build more 
advanced Path features 
What to expect 
July - September 2025: We'll update Path execution across all Zaps during this 
period.

📖 Product documentation: sequential path runs 
<https://help.zapier.com/hc/en-us/articles/37562074726029-Now-available-sequential-path-runs>
💬 Need help? Our support team <https://help.zapier.com/hc/en-us> is here. 

Thank you for using Zapier! We're excited about the improvements this change 
will enable.

Happy automating,
 The Zapier Team

subject: Professional Inquiry: Promo or Trial Option?
raw_subject: Professional Inquiry: Promo or Trial Option?
description:
Hi Team,

I’m reaching out with a direct and respectful request. I’m in the process of rebuilding my professional brand after a few difficult years—and a high-quality image is part of that.

I’ve tested several similar platforms, and I’ll be honest—many overpromised and underdelivered. I’ve seen misleading previews, poor final results, and support that vanished the moment payment cleared. So I’ve learned to approach these services with caution—and intentionality.

That’s why I’m reaching out to you. From what I’ve seen, BetterPic appears to be different: more polished, more ethical, and more invested in long-term trust. That matters to me. I work in public service, and while my budget is limited, I’m deeply loyal to companies that do right by their users.

If you offer any trial access, promo code, or entry-level discount, I’d love the opportunity to evaluate your service firsthand. If it’s as good as I suspect, you won’t just gain a customer—you’ll gain an advocate. I’ve built trust in communities that rely on strong word-of-mouth, and I’m always looking to share quality tools that actually deliver.

Either way, thank you for your time and your consideration.

Warm regards,
Jeffrey Meyers

Open to a quick chat?

subject: Recover More Revenue from Your Website Without Increasing Ad Spend
raw_subject: Recover More Revenue from Your Website Without Increasing Ad Spend
description:
Hello,

I’ve been following your company’s impressive work and growth through strategic advertising. But even with strong ad performance, there’s one challenge nearly every high-performing business faces: most website visitors leave without taking any action. In fact, over 97% of traffic typically bounces leaving a significant amount of potential revenue on the table.

At VIQ Concepts, we specialize in Retention Optimization, a conversion-first system that helps businesses like yours turn underperforming websites into high-converting customer journeys. Our approach doesn’t require increasing your ad spend. Instead, we focus on maximizing the value of the traffic you’re already generating.

We help companies:
1. Triple their conversions using the same traffic
2. Reduce bounce rates and eliminate dead-end user flows
3. Build loyalty and referral systems that increase customer lifetime value
4. Implement automated email flows to recover and convert cold leads

For your business, this means more revenue, better ROI from your current marketing efforts, and an overall smoother path from visitor to customer. This service can work alongside your existing strategies and integrates seamlessly without disrupting your current setup.

Would you be open to a quick 15-minute chat to explore how Retention Optimization could align with your current goals and unlock new growth opportunities?

Looking forward to connecting.

subject: Action required: Update your CMS publishing endpoints — July 7, 2025
raw_subject: Action required: Update your CMS publishing endpoints — July 7, 2025
description:
WebFlow Please see inside for more details 
 ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ 
⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ 
⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ 
⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ ⁣ 

 <https://webflow.com/?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email> 




Important changes for CMS publishing



We’re writing to let you know that we’re making updates to how you manage live 
items and publish CMS content via the API. As part of this change, you will 
need toupdate your code by July 7, 2025 to avoid disruption. 


We’ve covered the full details in the changelog 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/changelog?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
, but here’s a summary of what you need to know. 



What’s changing



Unpublishing live items
Previously, updating a live item’s isDraft property to true would unpublish it 
from the site. To support improved draft management, settingisDraft: true will 
now no longer unpublish the item. Instead, you can unpublish live items using 
theunpublish endpoint 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/reference/cms/collection-items/live-items/delete-items-live?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
. The item will remain live while draft updates can be made using staged item 
endpoints. 


Publish items when domains are out of sync
Good news! Those pesky 409 errors when publishing CMS items with out-of-sync 
domains? Gone! You can now publish items using thepublish items endpoint 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/reference/cms/collection-items/staged-items/publish-item?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 even when domains are out of sync. No code changes needed — it just works. 



Required actions



Please update your code to use either the Unpublish Single Item 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/v2.0.0/reference/cms/collection-items/live-items/delete-item-live?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 orUnpublish Multiple Items 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/v2.0.0/reference/cms/collection-items/live-items/delete-items-live?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 endpoint by July 7, 2025. 



Timeline & testing




 * Now through July 7: Test and update your code 
 * On July 7: Changes go live in v2 


Looking to test this functionality before the change? The new functionality is 
already live in ourBeta APIs 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/v2.0.0-beta/reference/cms/collection-items/staged-items/publish-item?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 — just switch/v2 to /beta in your API calls to test in your dev environment. 
Note: Webflow SDK doesn't support beta namespace yet. 



Resources




 * Full Changelog 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/changelog?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 * Forum Discussion 
<https://discourse.webflow.com/t/important-changes-to-cms-publishing/323920?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>
 * API Reference 
<https://developers.webflow.com/data/reference?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=apiupdates-july2025>


 We hope these updates make it easier for you to build and move faster in 
Webflow. We’re excited to get these improvements into your hands! 


Happy coding! ✨ 


 The Webflow DevRel team

raw_subject: Re: [Ai SuitUp] Your AI Generated Headshots Are Ready!
description:
I cannot use any of these. None of them look like me - 

- The images generated were too artificial looking. Not very natural - I look plastic in many of them! 
- They all just made me look like a young cartoon version of myself. My eyes were too far apart, or too big, or my lips were too big, or my boobs were too big, or my forehead was too pronounced. Nothing about them looked natural actually, now that I am writing this. - the distribution of my features was just all off, so I look distorted in every image. 
They all looked like a computer generated, too immaculate, too much photoshopping effects, which just ended up looking like an imaginary version of someone who is insecure or wanted to mislead the audience. I am neither of those things.  

- I am slender and athletic - so any pictures that showed my bust (from the waist up),  were not only incredibly inaccurate, but inappropriate looking for my professional appearance. Not only do I not have cleavage, but I would NEVER show it in my professional head shots as an executive. You may want to add this to your intake form for women…there is no way me or my peers (in our mid-40s would get away with showing cleavage and be taken seriously, or respected) 

I hope this is somewhat helpful. 

Please let me know what you can do to either refund or regenerate images for me. 
And, regardless, please delete all of these. 

Thank you, 
Gina

 <https://webflow.com/?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email> 



 Hi Ai, 


On June 3, Webflow experienced a service disruption that caused a temporary 
outage across all Webflow-hosted sites. We know how critical your websites are 
to your business and to your customers, and we’re deeply sorry for any 
disruption this incident caused. I want to ensure that we are taking ownership 
for this incident and working diligently around the clock to ensure a similar 
disruption never happens again. 


The issue stemmed from an internal backend update and a cache refresh that 
unexpectedly strained our systems, causing outages and degraded performance 
across some hosted sites, the Webflow Dashboard, and the Canvas. Our 
engineering and support teams responded rapidly, and while the core issue was 
stabilized within minutes, related performance issues persisted through the 
morning UTC as we worked to fully restore service. 


By early afternoon UTC, we had expanded capacity across multiple systems, 
resolved the underlying constraints, and achieved full stability. We’ve since 
completed an internal investigation to better understand the factors that 
contributed to the incident and ensure we’re taking the right steps to prevent 
this from happening again. 


Our promise to you: Performance and reliability are critical features that we 
will continue to invest in heavily. We sincerely appreciate your trust and 
partnership, and we’re committed to doing better. 


Sincerely, 


Allan Leinwand

description:
Hi team,

I have 2 major problems which makes all of these images unusable.

1. All of the shots have me with hair but I no longer have hair or have a very thin amount in some of my uploads as shown. I specified bald so I thought the image generator would make all the shots bald. When I do have hair my hair is curly but I would need all of these shots done with me bald.

2. For some reason all of the shots have me with some kind of bumps or protrusions in my forehead which I don't have in real life (you can also see this from my source photos)

3. There is a bit too much smoothing in all the shots which has them look AI-generated/ took airbrushed. If this can't be fixed I understand but would prefer shots that don't look so artificial.

Updating #1 and #2 are critical (especially #1) for all of my shots. If you are going to make updates please know I need more of the shots in a suit or a collared shirt as these are for professional headshots which is why I chose your service. I hope to hear from you soon. Thanks for your support with these issues.

Cheers,
Alexei

Estimado equipo de AI SuitUp,

Hemos utilizado hoy vuestro servicio para generar fotografías profesionales mediante IA. En primer lugar, solicitamos la generación de imágenes para mi pareja (Letizia.fascetto@icloud.com) y hemos quedado extremadamente satisfechos con el resultado.

Sin embargo, en mi caso particular (a.f.verdaguer@icloud.com), lamentablemente los resultados no han cumplido con nuestras expectativas. De las imágenes generadas, solamente una o dos reflejan adecuadamente mi apariencia real, mientras que el resto se perciben claramente como imágenes generadas por IA de baja calidad. Además, notamos cambios significativos en rasgos faciales, lo que hace que las fotografías no sean útiles para nuestro objetivo profesional.

Por lo anterior, solicitamos amablemente la devolución del importe pagado, o bien, un código de descuento del 100% para realizar una nueva solicitud con una selección diferente de fotografías iniciales, con el fin de obtener mejores resultados.

Quedamos atentos a vuestra pronta respuesta y solución al respecto.

Muchas gracias por vuestra atención.

Un cordial saludo,
Alejandro Verdaguer

Logic is going away next month



Throughout the past few months we communicated an important update 
<https://webflow.com/updates/deprecating-logic-and-user-accounts?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=eollogicanduser>
 regarding the future of Logic. We're following up with this reminder as these 
changes may affect your site. 


With Webflow's shift to a Website Experience Platform, we've made the 
strategic decision to no longer make Logic available in favor of our ecosystem 
of vetted app partners. 




Important dates:





June 27, 2025: Logic will no longer be available. Our top recommended partners 
areZapier 
<https://webflowlogic.zapier.app/homepage?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=eollogicanduser>
 andMake 
<https://dhygzobemt712.cloudfront.net/Web/resources/Webflow-Make-Logic_Offer.pdf?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=eollogicanduser>
. 


We’ve worked with our top ecosystem partners mentioned above to provide 
special discounts (linked above) for Webflow customers that are impacted by 
these changes. And if you need support from a certified Webflow agency partner, 
we’vehandpicked a list 
<http://webflow.com/certified-partners/migration-support?utm_source=iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=eollogicanduser>
 with the right expertise to assist you with your transition. 



For more details, visit this Help Center article

subject: Bug report (1) Misconfigured SPF
description:
Hi Team,
I found this vulnerability in                https://aisuitup.com
                    
Vulnerability Type: Misconfigured SPF
Description:
This report is about misconfigured spf record flag , which can be use to abuse the organization by posing the identity , which allowing to fake mailing on behalf of respected organization .

About the Issue :   
 as i seen the SPF and TXT record for the info@aisuitup.com                             

 Found v=spf1 record for aisuitup.com:
v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com include:mail.zendesk.com ~all




as u can see the symbol at last which (~all) is the issue , which should be replace by 
(-all) symbol .so valid record will be look like :   


 Found v=spf1 record for aisuitup.com:
v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com include:mail.zendesk.com -all



   What's the issue :

as u can see in the article difference between softmail and fail you should be using fail as Softmail allows anyone to send spoofed emails from your domains.

in current SPF record you should replace  ~ with - at last before all , ~ is strict which prevents all spoofed emails except if you are sending .
Attack Scenario :

an attacker will send phishing mail or anything malicious mail to the victim via mail info@aisuitup.com                              
 even if the victim is aware of phishing attack , he will check the Origin email which will be info@aisuitup.com                                
  so he will be sure that its not fake mail and get trapped by the attacker !
This can be done using any php mailer tool like this ,

<?php

$to = "VICTIM@example.com";

$subject = "Password Change";

$txt = "Change your password by visiting here - [VIRUS LINK HERE]l";

$headers = "From:  
 info@aisuitup.com

 ";
mail($to,$subject,$txt,$headers);

?>

u can check your SPF record form here :  https://www.kitterman.com/spf/getspf3.py  

Reference : https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-an-spf-record-to-prevent-spoofing-improve-e-mail-reliability

have a look at the digitalocean article for a better understanding !

Please let me know if you need more information.
Sincerely,Abdul Rehman

subject: Re: AI SuitUp - Headshots
description:
Hello Taylor! 
Support has not reached out, but given this is an urgent matter, I ask you kindly to escalate the following request to customer support leaders: 

--- 

Hi All! 
I'm Flavio Di Palo and I'm the Owner of Deep Rest LLC, the company operates a AI Headshots generation service (aisuitup.com) and RunPods is our main GPU provider for model fine-tuning.
We have identified an issue in our billing, in particular, starting from May 3rd 2025 our Average Daily Spent on RunPods has grown from $612.99 from $194.86 (daily average from April 13th to May 2nd). 

This growth is not associated with a growth in usage on our service hence we have investigated further. 
It turns out that several Pods have been running constantly on our account since May 3rd, those Pods have not shut down despite our code signaling to shut down once the model fine-tuning is completed. 
I have shut down those pods manually and I can provide the IDs for those executions if your technical team needs to investigate further.

As there has been no change in our code managing Run Pod interaction in the last 6 months we have to inpute this defect to an issue on RunPods Pods infrastructure management side.
For this issue we have been unjustly billed, and we already paid a total of $6,129.90 from May 3rd to May 13th vs. a projected cost of $1,753.76 (assuming same daily usage and cost of April 13th to May 2nd period). 

As we have all the reason to believe this was an issue on the Run Pod side we kindly demand you to: 
1. Reimburse the difference of $4,376.14 to our Credit Card on File. 
2. OR to provide a RunPod Credit for the total $6,129.90 to be used in the next 6 month,  to compensate for the hussle and the anticipated payment we have already finalized. 

Please find the data to used for this analysis reported in this Google Doc for completeness: 
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1eDHanKOb9P88VS-6S6L3v8KIq12mE1dsxfO1DRfNoDM/edit?usp=sharing

Please let us know if you are aware of any issue on your side that might have caused this. 
As we have always found a great partner in Run Pod we would prefer the "Credits" reimbursement option as we count on this service for the long run. 

I wish you a great day! 
Flavio.
Founder of DEEP REST LLC. 
ᐧ

subject: Re: [Ai SuitUp] How did we do?
raw_subject: Re: [Ai SuitUp] How did we do?
description:
Hi Simon,

Thanks for reaching out - I'd like to start with 2 pieces of honest feedback. 
Firstly, of all the various AI headshot generator tools I've tried recently, I felt that AI SuitUp had the highest # of photos out of the total photos generated that overall looked similar to my actual facial features (maybe 10 pounds lighter!). So, the accuracy to my real face, given the photos I uploaded, was impressive. The quality of the photos/backgrounds is crisp, clear.

The only drawback, which I was afraid of because I had similar issues with other tools as well, was the fact that only 3 photos were provided with hijab. Most of the photos I uploaded of myself include hijab. I wish that I could have had (all or at least some more photo options with hijab.

Is there any adjustment that can be done with the existing results? I'm overall happy with the photos it generated but because I wear hijab and these results only provided 3 or maybe 4 photos with hijab, they are not actually of use for me. 

Hoping your team can help,

Zainab

subject: Request for Redo – AI Headshots Did Not Accurately Reflect My Appearance
raw_subject: Request for Redo – AI Headshots Did Not Accurately Reflect My Appearance
description:
Dear AI Suit Up Team,

I recently purchased the Professional package and used your platform to generate a set of AI headshots and wanted to reach out regarding an issue I encountered with the final results.

While I appreciate the ease and overall quality of the renders, I noticed that the headshots produced do not accurately reflect my real-life appearance. I had selected the “Asian” setting during the generation process—as I am half Asian—but I am also half White and Pacific Islander. Unfortunately, the AI seems to have leaned heavily into the Asian features, resulting in headshots that my friends and family have confirmed do not look much like me. I am wondering if I chose a combination of races it may come out better? Or maybe since I appear more Asian I should have chosen White to balance it out?

Given that the system currently only allows for one ethnic selection, I understand this may have influenced the output. However, I was hoping for a more balanced and realistic representation. With that in mind, I’d like to request a redone set of headshots—ideally one that better reflects my mixed heritage and overall appearance. I’m happy to provide additional photos or input if that would help improve the result.

Please let me know what the next steps would be to move forward with this.

Thank you in advance for your time and assistance.

Best regards,
Brace Tyler
Btyler001@gmail.com

description:
Hey team,
Just got my results—some good stuff in there, but overall not quite what I was hoping for. Before I click the re-upload link, a few quick questions:

1. Should I upload an entirely new set of images?
2. Will the AI reference my original upload or just the new batch?
3. Any tips on image selection for better results this time around?

For context: I tried to match the final style by submitting mostly older selfies of me dressed up—same suit, same haircut, same day. I threw in a few recent ones, but not many. I assumed giving it the “best version” of me would help, but the results came out pretty homogenous and a bit dated (age, weight, etc.)—lesson learned.

So now I’m wondering:
– Should I include some of the same pics but add more variety?
– Or go all-new since the system may already "know" those images?

I don’t take many selfies, but I have tons of recent casual shots with friends I can crop. Would a mix of best-looking + more recent casual pics work better in your experience?

This is my first time using an AI image generation tool, so apologies if these are rookie questions. I can tell your tool’s solid—just hoping to dial in the output a bit more.

Thanks in advance,
Alfredo

description:
Hello, my name is Kris Hunter and I am the CEO of Blue Planet Academy, a marine life education and conservation organization.  In just a few weeks we will have a global presence on the web with a digital marine mammal naturalist certification training program.  There are five companies in the world who engage in this activity and they are all site specific, have an in person component, and are on 1-5 local marine mammal species.  Our program is worldwide, completely digital, covers the most commonly sighted 40 marine mammal species, has both certified and non-
certified options, and even discusses public speaking and the dreaded fear of the microphone!  There is a forum-open to anyone, a news blog, live Q and A from Kris Hunter, a marine mammalogist whose led over 6000 whale watches in three different oceans, pop quizzes, a open book final exam, and so much more.  Make a splash and join today!

What would a headshot package price for me?  Thank you for your time.

Kris Hunter
Blue Planet Academy 
831-406-0960
Info@blueplanetacademy.org

subject: RE: [Ai SuitUp] Your AI Generated Headshots Are Ready!
raw_subject: RE: [Ai SuitUp] Your AI Generated Headshots Are Ready!
description:
Hi,

Thanks for reaching out to us. We are sorry to hear that the quality of the pictures does not meet your expectations. Despite most customers being happy with the results, sometimes the pictures may have a below-average quality.

AI results greatly depend on user inputs; unfortunately, most of yours do not adhere to the guidelines. You can use the link below to try uploading different pictures and get better results for free:

https://web.aisuitup.com/new_order?coupon=CGXg2RSAXJU

Please carefully read these instructions before uploading the new pictures:

- Upload 15 frontal chest-up closeups taken in daylight. Do not upload full-body photos, too far away or too close (face cropped);
- Each photo must have a different background, lighting conditions, clothes, and a slightly different facial expression. Avoid repeating backgrounds, outfits, and pictures taken on the same day.
- Ensure you do not upload the same picture more than once.
- Ensure that you don't upload screenshots.
- Ensure your photos are good quality (>400 px). Do not upload dark, filtered (including b/w), post-produced, blurry, pixelated or AI generated pictures.
- Ensure that your entire face is not covered and is clearly visible. Do not upload pictures with hats/beanies, sunglasses, hands/arms, headphones, speaker sets, or eye patches.
- Ensure all the pictures are recent. Do not upload old pictures (e.g., completely different hairstyles or hair colors).
- Each picture should have only your entire face. Do not upload photos with others (not even partially there), animals, or objects covering your face (including phones, hair, hands, or glare from glasses).
- Avoid unprofessional/funny facial expressions (e.g., do not squint too hard) and exaggerated angles (e.g., side shots or photos taken from the top/bottom or while lying down).
- Ensure that you look into the camera in all the pictures and that your eye color is clearly visible.

If you are unhappy with your new results after uploading pictures adhering to the guidelines, I will gladly refund you.

We wish you a great day,
The AI SuitUp Team

* * *
Hello,

Can I get a refund? The images we got don’t look close enough like the actual person.

Thank you,

description:
Thank you for creating and sending.  This is my first time using your service, and while impressive, I noticed a few things:

1) the instructions about choosing body type were not clear to me.  I have a bigger, broad-shouldered, heavier male body type but the choices to select from seemed limited to feminine descriptions (curvy, plus-sized) that are not appropriate options for men.  So I chose "no preference" thinking that my body size would be accurate based on the photos I uploaded.  Unfortunately this is not the case in the vast majority of the headshots that were produced.  Most of the headshots do not reflect my body type so seem very fake.

2) in some of the photos the my hair is not touched up enough so appears frizzy and unprofessional.  This is especially the case in the one photo (3rd headshot) that does most accurately portray my body type/size.

3) my face/skin coloration, condition, and detail appear unnatural.  It looks great and very youthful but not super realistic, especially when looking up close.

How can these issues be addressed?  

Thank you.

Dan Ziony
Real Estate Advisor
Palo Alto | Menlo Park | Peninsula | Silicon Valley

DRE#: 01380339
650-201-1010

This is a follow-up to your previous request #8598 "Re: [Ai SuitUp] Your AI Gen..."

Good morning Chiara,

Thank you for your assistance. I tried the AI Suit Up upload again and unfortunately I don't think the images are suitable. Is it possible to obtain a refund?

If you'd like to relay feedback to the team working on this, my thoughts would be to:
-Limit variation in face shape and body shape
-Allow customers to choose which "outfit" works (I.e., if there is a photo that resembles you closely but it's in a turtleneck photograph and you need it in a suit and tie, this would be unusable.)
-Perhaps allow users to upload a video of themselves for a more realistic dynamic data input instead of something static like a photograph.

Thank you again.

Best,
Greg

subject: Feedback on AI SuitUp Headshot Generator Experience & Enquiry about Package Options
raw_subject: Feedback on AI SuitUp Headshot Generator Experience & Enquiry about Package Options
description:
Dear AI SuitUp Customer Service,

 

I’m writing to share some feedback on my “Executive / Ultimate” experience using the AI SuitUp Headshot Generator, and to enquire about next steps.

 

Overall, I found the process easy to navigate and not difficult to use. That said, I’ve noticed that some of your newer competitors are setting higher expectations by offering more variety in their photos such as the ability to toggle between wearing glasses or not, and more customisation options to adjust features like hair length, mouth & eye positions, and expressions.

 

While a few of the photos generated through AI SuitUp are usable for low-resolution purposes, I didn’t feel that any one image captured a version of me that I’m confident using for higher-resolution purposes. In several images, the positioning of my eyes appeared slightly off when glasses were rendered. In others, the glasses looked realistic, but the hairstyle didn’t reflect me. In some cases, the smile or teeth were noticeably inauthentic.

 

I am disappointed that the AI SuitUp generator did not offer a mix of with-glasses and without-glasses portraits, even though I included both types in my training photos. Many newer platforms provide both portraits and do so with as few as 8–12 input images. This flexibility in the final portraits allows users more choices to select what best represents them based on how the generator made them look with glasses vs without glasses.

 

With that in mind, I’m considering getting another set of portraits without glasses, which I’ve seen offered by other services. Before I do, I wanted to check whether AI SuitUp could include this option under the original “Executive / Ultimate” package I purchased.

 

To be clear, I’m not asking for a refund, but I’m also not fully satisfied with the current set of photos. If a set of photos of me “without glasses” would require a full repurchase, I may explore alternative providers.

 

Thanks in advance for your time, and I look forward to your response.

 

Kind regards,

Nancy Goletsos

I hope you're doing well! My name is Simone Restelli, founder of AI SuitUp (aisuitup.com), the pioneer in AI Headshots genertion.

I’ve personally been interviewed by _The Wall Street Journal_ as a subject matter expert in AI-generated headshots (WSJ article here).

I’m reaching out because I noticed you’ve already covered the topic of AI headshots in https://nairatips.com/best-ai-linkedin-photo-generators/, and I believe our latest model represents an outstanding addition to this growing field.

We’ve just released a new version of our algorithm, delivering the most photorealistic headshots available, powered by FLUX, an advanced text-to-image model developed by Black Forest Labs. Using the LORA technique, users can fine-tune the model with just a few selfies to create personalized, professional headshots.

You can learn more about our latest model and see some examples yourself in this detailed guide.

We are open to discussing options for a feature and, if you’re interested, I’d be happy to offer you access to our Beta for free so you can try it yourself. You can use this link to explore it.
